{{Infobox Website | name = Archive.is | logo = | screenshot = | caption = | url = [http://archive.is/ archive.is] | alexa = {{IncreaseNegative}} 36,051 ({{as of|2013|5|9|alt=May 2013}})<ref name="alexa">{{cite web |url=http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/archive.is |title=Archive.is Site Info |website=Site Info |publisher=[[Alexa Internet]] |accessdate=9 May 2013}}</ref><!--Updated monthly by OKBot.--> | commercial = No | type = | language = [[English language|English]] | registration = | owner = | author = | launch date = | current status = Online | revenue = | slogan = }} '''Archive.is''' is a privately funded digital [[time capsule]] with data-centre located in Europe at Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France.<ref name="statradar.com">{{cite web |url=http://www.statradar.com/www/archive.is |title=archive.is |publisher=Stat Radar |accessdate=8 May 2013}}</ref> The archive runs [[Apache Hadoop]] and [[Apache Accumulo]] software. It retrieves one page at a time similar to [[WebCite]], smaller than 50Mb each, but with [[Google Maps]] and [[Twitter]] included. Because it is not a free-walking [[Web crawler|crawler]] like [[Wayback Machine]], ''Archive.is'' does not obey robots. It captures textual content of web pages per request, as well as images, and content of frames, loaded or generated by [[Javascript]] on [[Web 2.0]] sites without active elements or scripts. Screenshots are of 1024x768 pixels, with no popups.<ref name="archive.is">{{cite web |url=http://archive.is/ |title=Archive.is – webpage capture |publisher=Archive.is |accessdate=8 May 2013}}</ref><ref name="archive.is/faq">{{cite web |url=http://archive.is/faq.html |title=FAQ |publisher=Archive.is |accessdate=8 May 2013}}</ref><ref name="blog.archive.is">{{cite web |url=http://blog.archive.is/archive |title=Archive.is blog – Archive |website=Archive.is blog |publisher=[[Tumblr]] |accessdate=8 May 2013}}</ref> This service is a tool that can be used to crawl and saves pages for use in citations in [[Wikipedia]] (see [[Wikipedia:Link rot#Repairing a dead link|Wikipedia:Link rot]] for additional info). <!-- Service is still under evaluation. -->
